<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,439,752]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,548,573]" pageId="2">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,430,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1460,1482]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,806,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[159,1444,804,1439]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of Afroperlodes lecerfi, Hemimelaena flaviventris and Isoperla cf. kir in the western Maghreb." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228488/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[417,430,548,572]" pageId="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). A North African endemic present in 
<collectingCountry box="[880,984,549,572]" name="Morocco" pageId="2">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[997,1081,548,573]" name="Algeria" pageId="2">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lounaci" box="[1098,1379,548,573]" pageId="2" refString="Lounaci, A. &amp; Vincon, G. (2005) Les Plecopteres de la Kabylie du Djurdjura (Algerie) et biogeographie des especes d'Afrique du Nord (Plecoptera). Ephemera, 6 (2), 109 - 124.] 2004]" type="journal article" year="2005">
Lounaci &amp; Vinçon 
<number box="[1321,1379,548,573]" pageId="2" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,234,583,608]" name="Tunisia" pageId="2">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Berthelemy" box="[249,868,583,608]" pageId="2" refString="Berthelemy, C. (1973) Donnees preliminaires sur les Plecopteres de Tunisie. Verhandlungen der internationalen Vereinigung fur Theoretische und Angewandte Limnologie, 18, 1544 - 1548." type="journal article" year="1973">
Berthélemy 
<number box="[390,449,584,608]" pageId="2" value="1973.0">1973</number>
, sub. nom. 
<taxonomicName box="[579,868,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Hemimelaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviventris">
<emphasis box="[579,868,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="2">Hemimelaena flaviventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</bibRefCitation>
) (Berthélemy 
<emphasis box="[1034,1094,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="2">in litt</emphasis>
. and G. Vinçon observations). In 
<collectingCountry box="[181,285,621,644]" name="Morocco" pageId="2">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, the species has been recorded in several localities in the High Atlas ranging between 
<date box="[1242,1408,620,645]" pageId="2" value="1000" valueMax="2650">
<number box="[1242,1298,620,644]" pageId="2" value="1000.0">1000</number>
and 
<quantity box="[1352,1408,620,645]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" pageId="2" unit="m" value="2650.0">2650</quantity>
</date>
m a.s.l., but also in the Rif between 
<number box="[525,567,656,680]" pageId="2" value="400.0">400</number>
and 
<quantity box="[621,709,656,680]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="2" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,439,752]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,692,717]" pageId="2">Ecology.</emphasis>
An orophilic species occurring in mountain brooks and torrents between 
<number box="[1155,1197,692,717]" pageId="2" value="450.0">450</number>
and 
<quantity box="[1257,1348,692,717]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="2" unit="m" value="2150.0">2150 m</quantity>
. Adults emerge during spring between May and June (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanchez-Ortega" box="[669,1038,727,752]" pageId="2" refString="Sanchez-Ortega, A. &amp; Azzouz, M. (1998) Faunistique et phenologie des Plecopteres (Insecta, Plecoptera) du Rif marocain (Afrique du Nord). Relations avec les autres aires de la region mediterraneenne occidentale. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 71, 449 - 461." type="journal article" year="1998">
Sánchez-Ortega &amp; Azzouz 
<number box="[978,1038,728,752]" pageId="2" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
